      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\">A 2-year-old boy is brought to the clinic by his mother, who is concerned about his failure to thrive and developmental delays. Karyotyping is performed, the result is shown below. What is the most common cardiac condition seen in this child?</span><br>&nbsp;</p><p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><img src=\"https://cerebellum-web-static.s3.amazonaws.com/media/public/images/2024/03/19/picture2_h3J4QWo.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"205\"></span></p><p style=\"text-align:justify;\">&nbsp;</p><p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\">What is the most common cardiac condition seen in this child?</span></p>",
      "unique_key": "Q8236047",
